These days, your mind's probably focused on the summertime, sweet summertime, with the perfect song on the radio. Well grab today's deal, and when the sun goes down, you'll be dreaming of groovin' to some quality country tunes... live. Spend $150 and receive two lower-level endzone tickets and a parking pass to see Kenny Chesney and Tim McGraw on Sunday, August 12 at FedExField (a $250 value). Or, pay $300 and score two floor seats to the show, access to a three-hour all-you-can-eat food buffet, water and sodas, and one parking pass (a $500 value). A warm summer night, a deal that fits just right; and your favorite artists live and amped-up at FedExField? That'll make even the burgundy-and-gold boys of fall reconsider their favorite season.

As Chesney’s set started, he popped up, guitar in hand, and took his post… from there, he rode a chair lift to the stage and filled the next two hours with hits and a few new songs… and lots of energy.

The Kansas City Star

Behind the scenes...


When two heavy-hitting country stars come out performing a co-written song on country's biggest night (the Country Music Awards), one can only expect them to take over the world... or at least high-volume stadiums for a dual summer concert tour. Not only is Kenny Chesney and Tim McGraw's Brothers of the Sun tour the first time these two country-rockin' heavyweights have traveled together in ten years, it's one of the hottest tickets this summer, with performances by Grace Potter & The Nocturnals and Jake Owen to boot. Come watch these two rock out to a slew of their own hits, new tracks from upcoming albums, and, of course, their joint single, Feel Like a Rock Star. After this show, you probably will.
